Sat May 16 00:16:39 UTC 2026 - Jan Engelhardt <jengelh@inai.de>

- Update to release 5.8
  * Options -m2, -m3 and -c2 were implemented for arbitrary
    quadrangulations.
  * Added quadrangulations of a disk (-qP or -QP).
  * Change the meaning of 'd' after the number of vertices to
    specify the number of vertices in the dual (i.e., the number of
    faces. This is valid only for triangulations and
    quadrangulations and illegal otherwise.

